manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: SLIP RESISTANT SKECHERS Slip-resistant sole meets or exceeds industry standards for coefficient of friction.

ELECTRICAL HAZARD SKECHERS Work Electrical Hazard (EH) footwear meets ASTM F2413-2011 EH requirements. Footwear is constructed to provide a secondary level of protection on surfaces that are substantially insulated against accidental contact with electrically energized objects. Footwear is tested to resist disruptive discharge to ground under the potential of 18kV 60Hz AC for one minute with no current flow in excess of one mill ampere under dry conditions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Surprise in the Snow
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this shoe as well as a pair of the Skecher Afterburn M tennis shoes. I wanted a dedicated work shoe, because I was going though my shoes pretty quickly from wearing the same pair all the time. So, being that I had already had two previous pairs of the “Afterburn” shoe, and burned through each of them in just over a year respectively, I decided to get another pair of them and also get a pair of the Cessnock Food Service Shoe strictly for work. Both pairs of shoes arrived yesterday, and today I wore the Food Service shoe (FSS) to work for the first time.I slipped them on and found them to be a perfect fit. They are very light weight and comfortable. Usually, I find new shoes need a few days of wear to break-in until they really conform to the shape of your foot and then begin to fit well, but that wasn’t the case with these FSS shoes; they fit perfectly the moment I put them on.I wore them all day at work and discovered something that really surprised me. We had a snowstorm today and got about 2” by the time I got to work, and had a good 7” by the end of my shift. I park outside so of course I have to brush the snow off the car. After doing so I knocked the snow off my shoes before getting into the car. I was surprised to see that the snow didn’t stick to the material on top of the shoes, it was as if there was a water repellant in/on the material. I was sort of wondering why my feet weren’t getting cold while I was cleaning off my car and I guess that explains it. Another surprise was the fact that these shoes make no sound when walking on a tile floor while having wet soles. The “Afterburn” tennis shoes squeak like a rusty hinge when the bottom of the shoe is wet and you walk across tile or other such surfaces, but the FSS’s, are quiet as a mouse, not a sound comes from them, you could almost call them Ninja shoes.As for the style, well that’s a personal preference and these shoes suit me just fine. I think they look sharp, and nobody even noticed I had a new pair of shoes on today.Durability is the unanswered question and being that I’ve only worn them one day, that question will remain unanswered for a while. If I can get a solid two years out of them, just wearing them to work, I will definitely buy them again and certainly would recommend them to a friend.I hope this review helps with your decision. Peace.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great, comfortable fit for a uniquely shaped foot.
reviews.reviewText: Bought a pair that was similar but a different style a year ago and had to replace them as I literally walked holes through the rubber soles. They were the best shoes I've ever had. Bought these put of necessity and while the shoes hurt to wear the first couple pf days, these took far less time than the last pair I owned and are even better.I have extremely wide feet at the toes due to growing up "toe-walking" with a very narrow heel, so on the rare occasion I can find shoes that fit my width even a little, my heel comes put when I walk. My feet would also rip them apart within months. The slightly stretchy material of these shoes accommodate my wide toes but keep my heels in place. My last pair didn't suffer any damage due to my feet and only due to normal wear and tear.I even bought a size 11 (no wide) and it fits my weird feet fantastically. If you have a similar issue with your feet, give them a try!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable, stylish and slip resistant
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. My teenage son needed slip resistant shoes for his new fast food restaurant job. I knew that style was just as important to him as comfort. After doing several searches I purchased the Sketches slip resistant shoes. They were worth every penny. They are well made, he really likes the look of them, they are comfortable, and easy to slip in and off and provide plenty of support and slip resistance. He needed them within 48 hours and they arrived the day after I ordered them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These shoes are amazingly comfortable, breatheable, waterproof, slip resistant, and warm. I work in a mechanic shop. Im on my feet 10+ hrs a day and these shoes are by far THE BEST work shoes i have ever came across. No aches or pains after a hards day work and the grip is absolutely incredible even in wet/oily situations hands down 10 STARS IF I COULD!!!! DEFINITELY WOULD BUY AGAIN AND AGAIN

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars PERFECT FOR BARTENDING!!!! Buy These NOW!
reviews.reviewText: I bartend at the theme parks in Orlando and average 10 miles plus a day, 6 days a week. I have burned through three different pairs of shoes in the past three months, until I found these! The conditions I am in are high volume wet conditions, and my feet stay perfectly dry in these shoes. The soles have the perfect height to keep the shoe dry, without being bulky preventing one from tripping over their own feet.I have a wide flat foot, and these shoes have PLENTY of room in them. I wear a 12W and order the same in these. When I first put them on, they feel really loose which caused concern, but after wearing them a few days, I actually like the feel of the “looseness” as there are ZERO pressure points on my feet with these shoes, and they are snug enough that blisters do not form. The toe box feels longer than a 12, but like I just stated, my feet do not slide in the shoes and no blisters form. I AM IN LOVE WITH THESE WORK SHOESThe shoes actually look great as well. I find myself throwing them on when heading out for casual fun too. I NEVER leave reviews, but decided to in hopes others may see this and helps them buy these shoes for the same relief. Stay comfortable my friends

reviews.reviewTitle: Easy to put on and remove, and comfortable
reviews.reviewText: Mens Skechers Cessnock Food Services Shoes are easy to put on and remove as there are no laces to deal with. The laces are purely decoratave. They are comfortable, have good traction, are easy to clean and they look good. I wear them as casual foot ware and I don't worry about them getting wet or dirty.

reviews.reviewTitle: Same brand, different size but excellent quality nevertheless
reviews.reviewText: I wear a US 9 sketchers usually but had to return this one for a US 8 as it was much larger than expected. Otherwise, this is a great shoe for moving around at work (I'm a healthcare worker) and the style fits most business and casual settings.
